1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
What if I told you cells have a built-in lifespan?

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:08,800
This is the Hayflick limit—where cells can only divide about 50 times.

3
00:00:08,800 --> 00:00:12,400
Every time they divide, they're inching closer to aging.

4
00:00:12,400 --> 00:00:14,800
This limit stems from telomere shortening.

5
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:18,000
When telomeres are too short, cells stop dividing.

6
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:21,600
Understanding this can unlock secrets to aging and health.

7
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:23,200
But, we’re still learning.

8
00:00:23,200 --> 00:00:26,400
Curious about how science can extend our lives?

9
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:28,000
Hit that follow button!
